main event: A witness reported seeing a bright white, pulsating object moving in the sky over Stratford, Connecticut in 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright white, pulsating light that moved at an estimated speed of 50 mph.
The object was visible for approximately 30 seconds before it moved behind a house and disappeared.
The witness said the object was about 1/3 the size of a match stick held at arm's length.
The witness called the authorities to report the sighting around 12:30 am on the same night.
The Air Force requested the witness fill out a detailed questionnaire to provide more information about the sighting.
